We are thrilled to officially launch Incito Schools Virtual Learning Lab (ISVLL). This resource will allow Incito Schools to continue to deliver on our promise to families "to inspire and provide our learners with daily opportunities to obtain extraordinary amounts of achievement and success." Families, your teachers have sent communication regarding learning, ARFF and procedures.
www.incitoschoolsvirtuallearninglab.org

We value this opportunity to partner with you to support continued learning, relationships and ARFF! Share your success photos, videos and stories using #ISVLL and tag us at @incito_schools_goodyear, Incito Schools-Phoenix, Incito Schools.

post_text:
Incito Families,

As shared during our most recent communication, we are providing an update to the COVID-19 action plan. In response to the Governor’s recent announcement, Incito Schools will share our plan of action as soon as we have received specific direction from the Charter Board, our Governing Board and Arizona Department of Education/Health as we are bound by multiple entities. We will provide food services as needed and will ensure we hold true to our commitment to provide instructional support during any school closure time. At this time, know that we are working diligently to gather all necessary information and will assure additional communication. We appreciate your partnership and the diligent focus on the education, health and safety of all Incito learners.

Our very own Merrick was recently on the radio! On KEZ 99.9, Beth and Friends hosts a segment called Kids Quiz. Merrick has been trying for a long time to get selected as a caller. He WAS selected and was so polite, on the phone, that both Beth and Mountain Main Jay gave him tickets to the Messy Fest. This was a proud moment for Incito Schools as Merrick truly reflected what it means to be an Incito Knight through politeness and kindness. Merrick was one of our learners that was previously "knighted" and continues to model the "Incito Way" in complete excellence. Listen to the radio segment via the link below:

https://www.mp3cutter.com/download/006365401-8293.mp3

post_text: Incoming 2nd graders spent summer school acting in the role of a paleontologists. They completed various activities such as digging for fossils, unlocking dinosaur vaults, and hunting for dinosaur eggs that used their math addition, subtraction and reading comprehension skills to collect items to create their dinosaur exhibit. On the last day of summer school, learners opened their dinosaur museum to other learners and shared the knowledge they’d learned throughout the dig with their audience.
